The &#8220;minimum kernel version&#8221; setting for glibc in slackwarearm-current is something I did not want to apply in my own ARM tree anyway. Lots of ARM devices run kernels that are in the 3.4.x or older range and the slackware-current minimum of 3.8.4 is undesired. I think that even the slackwarearm-current value of 3.4.0 is set too high. I will stick with the 2.6.32 I am using at the moment.</p>
